                Convection ovens use a fan to circulate hot air, providing
                faster and more even cooking. However, this added complexity
                introduces unique repair needs. Common issues include
                malfunctioning fans or motors, which can lead to uneven cooking
                or complete fan failure. Heating elements and control boards can
                also experience problems similar to those in standard electric
                ovens. Regular maintenance is crucial for convection ovens,
                including cleaning the fan and motor assembly and ensuring the
                air circulation system is functioning correctly. Addressing
                these issues promptly can help maintain the oven's efficiency
                and cooking performance.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
