                but this combination also means a wider range of potential
                repair needs. Issues can arise with the gas cooktop, such as
                igniter problems or gas valve malfunctions, and with the
                electric oven, such as heating element failures or thermostat
                inaccuracies. Given their complexity, dual fuel ovens may
                require more specialized repair services to address both gas and
                electric components. Regular maintenance is essential to keep
                both systems running smoothly, including checking gas
                connections and inspecting electrical elements to prevent costly
                breakdowns.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
