                Gas ovens can experience ignition problems, where the oven fails
                to ignite or takes an unusually long time to light. This can be
                due to a faulty igniter, blocked gas ports, or issues with the
                gas supply. A weak or worn-out igniter may not generate enough
                heat to ignite the gas, while debris or food particles can
                obstruct the gas ports, preventing efficient ignition. Regular
                cleaning and maintenance of the gas ports and igniter can help
                prevent these issues. If the problem persists, it may be
                necessary to replace the igniter or consult a professional to
                check the gas supply and connections.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
