                which can sometimes malfunction, leading to incomplete cleaning
                cycles or even damage to the oven components. The self-cleaning
                process typically involves heating the oven to extremely high
                temperatures to burn off food residues, which can strain the
                oven's components. Common issues include the oven door not
                unlocking after the cycle, error messages, or failure to reach
                the necessary temperature for cleaning. To mitigate these
                problems, ensure that the oven is properly maintained and that
                the self-cleaning feature is used according to the
                manufacturer's guidelines. In cases of persistent malfunctions,
                seeking professional assistance may be necessary to diagnose and
                fix the issue.
              </p>
