                The door gasket, or seal, is crucial for maintaining the oven's
                internal temperature by preventing heat from escaping. A worn or
                damaged gasket can lead to longer preheating times and
                inefficient cooking, which can increase your energy bills.
                Replacing the door gasket is a simple and cost-effective repair
                that can significantly improve your oven's efficiency. This
                issue is common across various oven brands and models, including
                built-in wall ovens and freestanding ranges. Ensuring the gasket
                is in good condition is essential for optimal oven performance.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
