                produce heat. A weak or malfunctioning igniter can lead to
                ignition problems, causing the oven to take longer to preheat or
                fail to heat altogether. Replacing a faulty igniter can resolve
                these issues and restore efficient heating. This repair is
                common in gas stoves and ovens, and the cost can vary depending
                on the model and brand. Ensuring the igniter functions correctly
                is essential for safe and effective cooking.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Convection Fan</h3>
