                The control board is the central hub of an oven's electronic
                functions, managing various settings and operations. A faulty
                control board can lead to a range of issues, from unresponsive
                controls to incorrect cooking settings. Replacing a defective
                control board can fix these problems and restore full
                functionality to the oven. This repair can be more complex and
                may involve higher labor costs, but it is essential for
                maintaining the oven's performance. This issue is common in
                modern ovens equipped with digital controls and touchscreens.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
