                <div class="FAQ">
                  <div class="fa">
                    <h3>Why does my stove work but not my oven?</h3>
                  </div>

                  <div class="fa_plus"></div>

                  <div class="fa_minus"></div>
                </div>

                <div class="questions">
                  <p>
                    When your stove works but the oven breaks, there could be
                    several reasons behind this issue:
                  </p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>Gas Supply Issue: </b>If you have a gas oven, but the
                      stove (which typically operates on gas) works fine while
                      the oven does not, there might be an issue with the gas
                      supply specifically to the oven. This could be due to a
                      malfunctioning gas valve or a blockage in the oven's
                      supply line.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Igniter Problems: </b>Gas ovens use an igniter to
                      ignite the gas and create the flame necessary for heating.
                      If the oven igniter is faulty or not working correctly, it
                      can prevent the oven from heating up while allowing the
                      stove burners to function normally.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Thermostat Malfunction: </b>The oven thermostat
                      regulates the temperature by controlling the flow of gas
                      or electricity to the heating elements. If the thermostat
                      is defective or out of calibration, it may not signal the
                      oven to heat up properly even though the stove burners
                      work fine.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Faulty Heating Element: </b>Electric ovens rely on
                      these to generate heat. If one or more of these elements
                      is faulty or burned out, it can prevent the oven from
                      heating while the stove continues to operate normally.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Control Panel Malfunctions: </b>The control board
                      serves as the "brain" of the oven, governing its various
                      functions and settings. If the control board is
                      malfunctioning or has failed, it may not send the
                      necessary signals to the oven components to initiate the
                      heating process.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Wiring Problems: </b>An electric oven requires proper
                      wiring to supply power to the heating elements and other
                      components. If there are issues with the wiring, such as
                      loose connections or damaged wires, it can disrupt the
                      flow of electricity to the oven while allowing the stove
                      to function.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Internal Component Failures: </b>Various components
                      within the oven, such as relays, switches, or sensors, can
                      fail over time due to wear and tear or other factors. If
                      any of these components fail, the oven may not heat
                      correctly while the stove remains operational.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    While some oven and stove repairs may seem straightforward,
                    it's essential to recognize that attempting DIY repairs can
                    pose risks, especially if you're not familiar with appliance
                    maintenance or lack the necessary skills and tools.
                    Additionally, the cost to repair any mistakes made during
                    the DIY process can outweigh the savings.
